cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.CC 

The paper discusses the combination of SAT solvers and computer algebra systems for solving mathematical problems, which involves automated reasoning and search algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Other likely categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) for the use of automated reasoning, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) for the use of search algorithms and combinatorial spaces, and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) for the analysis of the efficiency and complexity of the combined approach.
